         <h1>Vittorio Rieti, Prolific Composer In Neo-Classical Style, Dies at 96 </h1>
           <div class="row">
               <div class="col-md-10">
 					<p class="text-left">
<blue>1</blue>Vittorio Rieti , a prolific American composer who fashioned bright , elegant Neo-Classical scores for the ballets of Serge Diaghilev and George Balanchine , died on Saturday at Mount Sinai Medical Center in Manhattan . <br><blue>2</blue>He was 96 and lived in Manhattan . <br><blue>3</blue>The cause was not immediately clear , said his son , Fabio , but Mr. Rieti had suffered a bad fall at his home , breaking several ribs . <br><blue>4</blue>In a career that spanned eight decades , Mr. Rieti wrote music for more than a dozen ballets , seven operas , five symphonies , several concertos , chamber music for a wide variety of instrumental combinations , songs and choral works . <br><blue>5</blue>His music was widely performed ; among the conductors who led performances of Mr. Rieti 's works were Fritz Reiner , Frederick Stock , Willem Mengelberg and Arturo Toscanini . <br><blue>6</blue>Mr. Rieti was born in Egypt , to Italian-born parents , and educated in Italy . <br><blue>7</blue>But his music -- in its wit , craft , lack of pretense and economy of means -- shares similarities with the work of the French group of composers who called themselves Les Six , particularly that of Poulenc . <br><blue>8</blue>The music of Stravinsky , a close friend , was also an important influence . <br><blue>9</blue>Mr. Rieti continued to compose until shortly before his death . <br><blue>10</blue>He used to say , " Composing every day is what keeps me alive . " <br><blue>11</blue>In his 75th , 80th and 85th birthday years , there were commemorative concerts in New York that included many new works . <br><blue>12</blue>" Vittorio Rieti is becoming something of a wonder , " Allen Hughes wrote in The New York Times after a 1985 concert . <br><blue>13</blue>" He will be 87 years old on the 28th of this month , but he is still composing music that is as sprightly and cheerful as anything he ever wrote . " <br><blue>14</blue>Other commentators remarked upon the jaunty cheer in Mr. Rieti 's music , yet some professed to find its obverse as well . <br><blue>15</blue>" Rieti 's oeuvre stands apart in its specific clarity , gaiety and sophistication of a kind only he possesses , " the composer Alfredo Casella once said , " yet it hides a good deal of melancholia . " <br><blue>16</blue>In 1973 , Mr Rieti said : " I go on writing music . <br><blue>17</blue>I started when I was 12 , and it has become a habit . <br><blue>18</blue>I maintain the same esthetic assumptions I have always had . <br><blue>19</blue>I have kept evolving in the sense that one keeps on perfecting the same ground . " <br><blue>20</blue>Three and Six Mr. Rieti was born in Alexandria , Egypt , on Jan. 28 , 1898 . <br><hr><br><blue>1(32)</blue>: <m_str>Rieti 's</m_str> (15_2) 	<m_str>Mr Rieti</m_str> (16_4) 	<m_str>I</m_str> (16_9) 	<m_str>Mr. Rieti</m_str> (9_1) 	<m_str>his</m_str> (9_9) 	<m_str>I</m_str> (17_1) 	<m_str>He</m_str> (2_1) 	<m_str>I</m_str> (17_4) 	<m_str>He</m_str> (10_1) 	<m_str>I</m_str> (18_1) 	<m_str>me</m_str> (10_13) 	<m_str>I</m_str> (18_7) 	<m_str>his</m_str> (3_9) 	<m_str>his son , Fabio</m_str> (3_9) 	<m_str>his</m_str> (11_2) 	<m_str>Fabio</m_str> (3_12) 	<m_str>Mr. Rieti</m_str> (3_15) 	<m_str>I</m_str> (19_1) 	<m_str>his</m_str> (3_23) 	<m_str>Mr. Rieti</m_str> (4_9) 	<m_str>Vittorio Rieti</m_str> (12_2) 	<m_str>His</m_str> (5_1) 	<m_str>Allen Hughes</m_str> (12_12) 	<m_str>Six Mr. Rieti</m_str> (20_3) 	<m_str>He</m_str> (13_2) 	<m_str>Mr. Rieti 's</m_str> (5_14) 	<m_str>Mr. Rieti</m_str> (6_1) 	<m_str>he</m_str> (13_16) 	<m_str>Mr. Rieti 's</m_str> (14_9) 	<m_str>his</m_str> (7_2) 	<m_str>he</m_str> (13_29) 	<m_str>its</m_str> (7_6) 	<br><blue>2(1)</blue>: <m_str>the composer Alfredo Casella</m_str> (15_23) 	<br><blue>3(3)</blue>: <m_str>music</m_str> (4_12) 	<m_str>His music</m_str> (5_1) 	<m_str>Mr. Rieti 's music</m_str> (14_9) 	<br><blue>4(1)</blue>: <m_str>Stravinsky</m_str> (8_4) 	<br><blue>5(2)</blue>: <m_str>Manhattan</m_str> (1_34) 	<m_str>M